# AdGo — AI Ad Automation Platform

An AI-driven ad automation platform: a business describes itself, Claude generates an ad
strategy (audiences, budget split, creatives), a campaign orchestrator launches it across
Meta and Google, a performance pipeline ingests results, a bandit-based optimization engine
reallocates budget toward winners, and a CRM sync pipeline pushes leads back to the
business's own systems.

## Architecture

The backend is split into several small services (`apps/*`), fronted by `apps/api` as the
gateway, plus a Python microservice used only for AI-assisted web scraping:

```
apps/web             Frontend — onboarding + dashboard (React/Vite)
apps/api             Gateway + core domain logic (Express + Prisma/Postgres):
  gateway/             Auth (JWT), rate limiting, routing to the other services
  modules/strategy/    Claude-based strategy generation (falls back to a
                       deterministic mock if ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is unset)
  modules/orchestrator/ Builds campaigns from a strategy, launches/pauses
                       variants via ad network adapters
  modules/adapters/    Meta + Google + TikTok Ads clients (mock data unless
                       live credentials are configured — see below)
  modules/integrations/ OAuth connections (Meta, Google) + product catalog
                       adapters (Shopify, WooCommerce)
  modules/onboarding/  Business scraping + AI market research
  modules/generation/  AI creative generation (image/video providers)
  modules/leadgen/     Lead ingestion + Meta/Google lead sync, contacts
  modules/crm/         Outbound CRM webhook delivery for synced leads
  modules/audience/    Saved audience management
  modules/pipeline/    Ingests raw ad-network insights, normalizes into
                       CTR / conversion rate / CPA per variant
  modules/adInsights/, modules/analytics/, modules/insights/
                       Ad performance and analytics rollups
  modules/optimization/ Epsilon-greedy bandit: exploits the best-scoring
                       variant, explores others, pauses high-CPA variants
  modules/billing/     Usage-based invoicing: flat fee + % of ad spend
  workers/             Background jobs (BullMQ/Redis): research sessions,
                       lead ingestion, CRM webhooks, metrics ingestion,
                       creative generation
apps/auth-service     Standalone auth microservice
apps/campaign-service Standalone campaign microservice
apps/scraper-service  Scraping/pipeline microservice (Node) that in turn
                       calls a Python sidecar (see below) for AI scraping
```

### Python scraping sidecar (`apps/scraper-service/python`)

`research_server.py` is a FastAPI service built on `scrapegraphai` that performs
LLM-assisted structured scraping for onboarding/market-research. Install its deps
separately (a virtualenv is recommended):

```bash
cd apps/scraper-service/python
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn research_server:app --port 5055
```

`apps/api` and `apps/scraper-service` call it via `SCRAPEGRAPH_SERVICE_URL`.

## Setup

```bash
npm install
cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env   # fill in keys you have; most are optional
npm run db:migrate --workspace apps/api  # requires DATABASE_URL (Postgres) + Redis running
npm run dev:api               # http://localhost:4000
npm run dev:web               # http://localhost:5173 (or next free port)
npm run dev:auth-service      # http://localhost:4001
npm run dev:campaign-service  # http://localhost:4002
npm run dev:scraper-service   # http://localhost:4003
```

On Windows, `npm run dev` (root) does not run both apps in parallel — start `dev:api` and
`dev:web` in separate terminals instead.

Open the web app, complete onboarding, generate a strategy, and launch a campaign. Use
"Pull latest metrics" and "Run optimization pass" on a campaign's detail page to exercise
the performance/optimization feedback loop, and generate an invoice from the Billing page.

### Environment variables (`apps/api/.env`)

Service URLs and internal auth (`INTERNAL_SERVICE_KEY`, `CRM_INTERNAL_SERVICE_KEY`) are
required to talk to the other services. External ad/AI integrations are optional in
development — every adapter falls back to deterministic mock data:

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — enables real Claude-generated strategies (Claude Sonnet 5)
- `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `RUNWAY_API_KEY` — enable real AI creative generation
- `META_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID` / `META_APP_ID`, `META_APP_SECRET` — Meta
  Marketing API + OAuth
- `GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN`, `GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID`, `GOOGLE_ADS_ACCESS_TOKEN` /
  `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_ID`, `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET` — Google Ads API + OAuth
- `TIKTOK_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `TIKTOK_ADVERTISER_ID` — TikTok Ads API
- `SHOPIFY_*`, `WOOCOMMERCE_*` — product catalog sync
- `TOKEN_ENCRYPTION_KEY` — encrypts OAuth tokens at rest
- `DATABASE_URL`, `REDIS_URL` — Postgres (Prisma) and Redis (BullMQ queues, caching)

## Data model (Postgres / Prisma)

`apps/api/prisma/schema.prisma` is the live production schema and is wired into the running
app via Prisma: Organization/User (tenancy), Business + ScrapedPage (onboarding),
OAuthConnection (encrypted-at-rest tokens), Strategy + Creative (AI output, held in
DRAFT/IN_REVIEW until approved), Campaign + CampaignCreative (per-network launch state),
Metric (daily performance), OptimizationAction (audit log of automated pause/budget
changes), Contact + lead sync state, CRM webhook config, Notification, and
Subscription/UsageRecord/Invoice (usage billing). Migrations live under
`apps/api/prisma/migrations/`.

## Notes

This is an original scaffold built around the product category adsgo.ai operates in
(AI-generated ad strategy + cross-network automation), not a copy of its code, text, or
design assets.
